      <section eId="sec_CHC-1562">
        <num>CHC 1562</num>
        <heading>1562. Â Immunity</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1562__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>In the opinion of the hospital, physician, or other person authorized by law to provide medical or surgical care, exercising competent medical judgment, the child's life would be threatened by delaying the provision of medical care or treatment.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1562__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The child's parent or guardian has wrongfully refused to consent to such medical care or treatment.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=73020</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
